article.headline: Penn 35, Cornell 28
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Andrew Holland drove Pennsylvania to a go-ahead score with a minute left as the Quakers clinched their 13th outright Ivy League title -- and 16th overall -- with a 35-28 victory Saturday over Cornell. Cornell's ensuing drive ran out of time at the 8-yard line of Penn (6-4, 6-1). Holland, starting because Billy Ragone was injured last week, completed three passes on Penn's final 63-yard drive, setting up Spencer Kulcsar's 3-yard scoring run. Luke Hagy rushed for two fourth-quarter touchdowns for the Big Red (4-6, 2-5), who tied the game at 28 on a 2-point conversion pass from Jeff Mathews to Luke Tasker. Mathews threw for 445 yards, completing 31 of 45. Penn took a 14-13 lead 26 seconds before halftime on Holland's 41-yard pass to Jason Seifert. They increased their lead to 28-13 on Lyle Marsh's 55-yard scoring run and Holland's 1-yard run after Tasker fumbled a punt.
